page.title: 10A DAY IN THE LIFE OF ANDREW
page.content: Most days my five year old brother wakes me up around seven a.m but on Saturdays he lets me sleep.I awake around eight forty-five a.m.I get up at ten minutes past nine.I have my cereal and go out.My friend is always waiting for me on the green with his ball.We then go over to the park and kick the ball to each other.Around eleven thirty a.m he tells me he wants his breakfast.After dinner we go for a bike ride mostly we bike down to the{Adventure play ground}until five p.m then to his bedroom to talk about girls.Soon his thirteen year old brother walks in and says I have just had my breakfast because to my friend's brother bed is the best place to be on a cold day. I go to bed at ten on Fridays and Saturdays.
